rules.description: allow copying, pasting and cutting when both command keys are pressed down (does not work yet)
cmd + caps_lock -> cmd + ctrl (some programs had problems with the reprogrammed caps_lock)
shift + caps_lock -> shift + ctrl (some programs had problems with the reprogrammed caps_lock)
fn + caps_lock -> caps_lock (for reprogrammed caps_lock incase caps_lock is toggled somehow)
caps_lock -> \ (shift-alt-7) if pressed alone; if not pressed alone ctrl
Map fn + number keys to their corresponding function keys. Only works if 'Use all F1, F2, etc. keys as standard function keys' is set under Function Keys.
